 separate origin, the former derived from <i>eu</i> ‘well, good’ + <i>stakhys</i> ‘grapes’, the latter from <i>eu</i> + <i>stēnai</i> ‘to stand’. However, the tradition is very confused. The name was introduced in this form to Britain by the Normans, among whom it was popular as a result of the fame of  St Eustace , a Norman nobleman who was said to have been converted to Christianity by the vision of a crucifix between the antlers of the stag he was hunting."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Eustace d'Arderne was born in 1140, in Watford, Northamptonshire, England, his father, Alexander d'Arderne, was 24 and his mother, Agnes D'arden, was 20. He had at least 1 son with Agnes of Watford. He died in 1213, in Aldford, Cheshire, England, at the age of 73."},"et":{"1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1116":"1116","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1116":"1116","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1116":"1116","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, Angleterre","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, Angleterre","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Eustace d'Arderne est né en 1140, à Watford, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, son père, Alexander d'Arderne, avait 24 ans et sa mère, Agnes D'arden, avait 20 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Agnes of Watford. Il est décédé en 1213, à Aldford, Cheshire, Angleterre, à l’âge de 73 ans."},"de":{"1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1116":"1116","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Eustace d'Arderne 1140 in Watford, Northamptonshire, England geboren wurde, war sein Vater Alexander d'Arderne 24 und seine Mutter Agnes D'arden 20. Er hatte mit Agnes of Watford mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1213 im Alter von 73 Jahren in Aldford, Cheshire, England."},"ht":{"1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1116":"1116","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Angletè, United Kingdom"},"hu":{"1140–1213":"1140–1213","1145–1200":"1145–1200","1165–1213":"1165–1213","1116–1165":"1116–1165","1120–1145":"1120–1145","1116":"1116","1213":"1213","1145":"1145","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","Alvanley, Cheshire, England":"Alvanley, Cheshire, England","Aldford, Cheshire, England":"Aldford, Cheshire, England","Watford, Northamptonshire, England":"Watford, Northamptonshire, Anglia, United Kingdom"},"id":{"1140–1213":"1140